
[1]concise

   CONCISE, a. [L., cut off, brief, to cut. See Class Gd. No. 2. 4. 8. 49.
   59.] Brief; short, applied to language or stile; containing few words;
   comprehensive; comprehending much in few words, or the principal
   matters only.

   The concise stile, which expresseth not enough, but leaves somewhat to
   be understood.

   Where the author is too brief and concise, amplify a little.

   In Genesis, we have a concise account of the creation.
